  "response_text": "A leafy outdoor path appears in a sunny residential or park-like setting, with shrubs, grass, and trees casting shade. Beside the path is a large rectangular street sign mounted on a gray post. The sign has a pale yellow face with a black border and bold black lettering that reads “PLEASANT” over smaller “STREET.” A light-skinned adult woman with a short blonde-brown bob walks along the path beneath the sign. She wears a light plaid button-up shirt and light-colored pants. As she comes closer, her face looks strained and uncomfortable.\n\nShe suddenly opens her mouth as if about to sneeze, then lifts a white tissue to her nose and mouth with both hands. Her eyes squeeze shut, her head dips forward, and she hunches slightly over the tissue, showing the discomfort of hay fever or a cold. The view returns to the street sign, and the words on it change from “PLEASANT STREET” to “HAYFEVER STREET,” keeping the same sign shape, colors, and post but replacing the friendly name with the illness-related one.\n\nThe commercial then shows the product package by itself against a plain light background. It is a rectangular Dristan box with a brown-orange top panel and white lower panel. Large white letters on the brown-orange panel read “DRISTAN,” with “DECONGESTANT TABLETS” underneath. The white area below includes the visible wording “SYMPTOMATIC RELIEF OF COLDS & HAY FEVER SINUS CONGESTION.”\n\nNext, several medicines are displayed on a clean white surface for comparison. On the left lies a red transparent capsule with many tiny pink-and-white beads inside. Behind it is a long pale beige oblong tablet or capsule shape, and in front is a flat round blue tablet. A separate round yellow tablet appears to the right, set apart from the others, with the label “DRISTAN” printed below it in black. The words “EXTRA MEDICINE” then appear above and near the Dristan tablet, visually emphasizing that the yellow Dristan tablet has something additional compared with the other medicine forms.\n\nThe scene returns outdoors to the same woman in a green yard with trees and bushes. She is now crouched beside a medium-to-large dark brown dog with floppy ears. White on-screen text at the bottom reads “USE ONLY AS DIRECTED.” The woman bends down affectionately, putting her arms around the dog and holding its collar or leash. Her expression is now cheerful and relaxed. She hugs the dog close, smiling broadly, while the dog faces to the side calmly. The lawn and shrubbery behind them are sunlit, and the woman appears comfortable and active again.\n\nThe “HAYFEVER STREET” sign appears once more on its gray post, still in the leafy outdoor setting. Then the sign changes into a product-style sign for Dristan, using the same suspended sign position. It shows the Dristan package design with the visible words “DRISTAN,” “DECONGESTANT TABLETS,” “COLDS & HAY FEVER,” and “SINUS CONGESTION.” Across the lower part of the screen, large white capital letters read, “EXTRA RELIEF MEDICINE THE OTHERS DON’T HAVE.” In the background near the path, the woman and her dark dog pass by, reinforcing the image of her being well enough to be outside and moving comfortably again.",
